ðŸ§© Step 4: Create Nginx config
Create docker/nginx/default.conf:

nginx
Copy
Edit
server {
    listen 80;
    index index.php index.html;
    server_name localhost;
    root /var/www/html/public;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.php?$query_string;
    }

    location ~ \.php$ {
        include fastcgi_params;
        fastcgi_pass app:9000;
        fastcgi_index index.php;
        fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME $realpath_root$fastcgi_script_name;
        fastcgi_param DOCUMENT_ROOT $realpath_root;
    }

    location ~ /\.ht {
        deny all;
    }
}
âœ… Important:

fastcgi_pass app:9000; (because your PHP container is named app in docker-compose)

Serving from /public

ðŸ§© Step 5: Setup .env for Laravel
In your Laravel project, check .env:

dotenv
Copy
Edit
APP_NAME=Laravel
APP_ENV=local
APP_KEY=base64:xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
APP_DEBUG=true
APP_URL=http://localhost:8080

LOG_CHANNEL=stack

DB_CONNECTION=mysql
DB_HOST=mysql-db
DB_PORT=3306
DB_DATABASE=laravel_db
DB_USERNAME=laravel_user
DB_PASSWORD=laravel_password
âœ… Important:

DB_HOST=mysql-db (service name, not 127.0.0.1)

APP_URL=http://localhost:8080

ðŸ§© Step 6: Build and Run
Now run:

docker-compose up -d --build
  
It will:

Build your PHP container

Start MySQL

Start Nginx

Connect everything

âœ… Wait 1â€“2 mins for MySQL to initialize.

ðŸ§© Step 7: Install Laravel (optional)
If you didn't install Laravel yet:

  
docker exec -it backend-pos-app bash
composer create-project laravel/laravel .
exit
Then:


docker-compose restart
âœ… If Laravel already exists, just skip.

ðŸ§© Step 8: Set permissions inside container
Run:

docker exec -it backend-pos-app bash
chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/html
chmod -R 775 storage bootstrap/cache
exit
âœ… Necessary for Laravel to work properly.

ðŸ§© Step 9: Visit the site ðŸŽ‰
Open your browser:


http://localhost:8080
âœ… You should now see the Laravel 12 welcome page!

ðŸš€ Bonus Commands
Command	Purpose
docker-compose ps	See running containers
docker-compose logs	See full logs
docker exec -it backend-pos-app bash	SSH into PHP container
docker-compose down	Stop all containers
docker-compose up -d	Start all containers
